    historicalContext: "Blue was released in June 1971, right as the idealism of the 1960s was visibly unraveling — the Summer of Love had given way to Altamont, Vietnam, and social fracture. Mitchell made no protest songs; instead she went inward, writing about heartbreak, travel, loneliness, and the search for freedom. In doing so she captured something the era's bigger statements missed: what it actually felt like to be alive and uncertain in that moment.",
