    historicalContext: "Grace arrived in August 1994, just months after Kurt Cobain's death had sent grunge into mourning. While the mainstream was absorbing that loss, Buckley was doing something completely different — making art rock that drew on Led Zeppelin, Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan, and Nina Simone instead of punk. He had built a following playing solo in a small New York club called Sin-é, and Grace captured that intimate intensity while adding a full band. His accidental drowning in 1997 at age 30 cemented the album's mythological status.",
