    artistOverview: "LCD Soundsystem was the project of James Murphy, a New York musician and producer who co-founded DFA Records in 2001 after years working as a sound engineer. Murphy came to dance music as a rock fan, and to rock as someone who loved dance music — the collision produced something that fit neither category comfortably. He was 37 when Sound of Silver was released, making him one of the oldest artists ever to release a breakthrough record, and many of the album's themes — aging, loss, the passage of time — reflect that perspective directly. LCD Soundsystem formally disbanded in 2011 and reformed in 2015.",
