    historicalContext: "Achtung Baby was recorded in 1990–1991, a moment of massive global transition. The Berlin Wall had fallen in November 1989, German reunification was underway, and the Cold War's binary certainties were dissolving. U2 went to Berlin partly to absorb that energy of historical change and partly to escape their own increasingly bloated reputation. The album arrived the same year as Nirvana's Nevermind — a year when alternative music suddenly dominated the mainstream — and Achtung Baby positioned U2 as part of that wave rather than a relic of the 1980s.",
