      "historicalContext": "What's Going On was released in May 1971, six years into the Vietnam War and just one year after the Kent State shootings. American cities had been rocked by civil rights uprisings, and Gaye's younger brother Frankie had returned from Vietnam deeply shaken. Motown records had largely avoided political content to stay on mainstream radio, but Gaye — inspired in part by a song brought to him by Four Tops singer Renaldo 'Obie' Benson — insisted on recording the album despite Berry Gordy's initial refusal to release it.",
