      "artistOverview": "Joy Division were a post-punk band from Salford, Greater Manchester, formed in 1976. The four members — Ian Curtis, Bernard Sumner, Peter Hook, and Stephen Morris — created a sound built on Hook's melodic bass lines, Sumner's sparse guitar, Morris's metronomic drumming, and Curtis's low, intense baritone. Curtis suffered from severe epilepsy and depression, and his lyrics drew heavily on alienation and loss. He died by suicide in May 1980, just before the band's first US tour; the remaining members reformed as New Order.",
