      "discussionQuestions": [
          "Carole King spent a decade writing hits for other singers before anyone knew her name. Is there something unfair about how the music industry treats songwriters compared to performers?",
          "Several songs on Tapestry are about heartbreak and loss. Why do sad songs often feel comforting rather than just depressing?",
          "Tapestry was marketed to adults in 1971 but has found new audiences in every decade since. What makes a record feel timeless rather than dated?",
          "'You've Got a Friend' was written as a gift for James Taylor, who also had a hit recording of it. Can you think of other examples where a song is famous in multiple versions — and does that dilute or multiply its meaning?"
      ],
