          "productionStyle": "Warm and organic — recorded at Island's Basing Street Studios in London. Karl Pitterson's mix gives the bass and drums unusual depth and clarity.",
          "energy": "Deceptively relaxed — the groove is steady and hypnotic, but the spiritual and political urgency underneath is constant",
          "keyIdea": "Exodus turns the Rastafari concept of spiritual liberation into a physical, musical journey — the rhythm itself feels like movement toward freedom."
