      "contentNotes": {
          "language": "moderate",
          "themes": "Several tracks contain sexual content in the lyrics ('If I Was Your Girlfriend,' 'Hot Thing,' 'It,' 'Adore'). 'Strange Relationship' and 'I Could Never Take the Place of Your Man' deal with adult romantic and sexual themes. The title track references gang violence, drug addiction, and AIDS. Teacher preview recommended; consider which tracks to feature in the classroom session.",
          "artworkConcern": "",
          "cleanVersionAvailable": "",
          "teacherDecision": ""
      },
      "classroomSafeMode": false,
      "keyFacts": [
          "Prince played nearly every instrument on the album himself — guitar, bass, keyboards, drums, piano, synthesizers, and all lead and backing vocals.",
          "The album was assembled from three scrapped projects: Dream Factory, an abandoned collaboration with The Revolution; Camille, a side project using a pitch-shifted vocal; and Crystal Ball, a planned 3-LP set that Warner Bros. rejected.",
          "The title track name-checks gang violence, crack cocaine, AIDS, and a tornado in its opening verse — a remarkable compression of mid-1980s American crisis.",
          "Rolling Stone ranked Sign 'O' the Times at #23 on its 2020 list of the 500 Greatest Albums of All Time."
      ],
      "keySongs": [
          {
              "title": "Sign 'O' the Times",
              "note": "The album's devastating opener — a sparse, urgent funk track that catalogues the crises of 1987 America. One of the greatest opening tracks in pop history."
          },
          {
              "title": "If I Was Your Girlfriend",
              "note": "One of Prince's most experimental and emotionally complex songs — he uses a pitch-shifted voice ('Camille') to explore gender, vulnerability, and intimacy in ways that were genuinely ahead of their time."
          },
          {
              "title": "U Got the Look",
              "note": "The album's most commercial moment — a hard rock and funk hybrid featuring Sheena Easton. Shows Prince's range from the spare title track to radio-ready pop-rock."
          },
          {
              "title": "The Cross",
              "note": "A slow build that explodes into a hard rock anthem — Prince's most overtly spiritual statement on the album. Shows how wide the album's emotional and sonic range truly is."
          }
      ],
      "tracklist": [
        { title: "Sign 'O' the Times", displayTitle: "Sign 'O' the Times", duration: "4:57", single: true, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "Reaching US #3, this socially panoramic opener catalogs AIDS, gang violence, drug addiction, and natural disaster in a stark, nearly percussion-free arrangement that is among Prince's greatest lyrical achievements." },
        { title: "Play in the Sunshine", displayTitle: "Play in the Sunshine", duration: "5:04", single: false, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "" },
        { title: "Housequake", displayTitle: "Housequake", duration: "4:41", single: false, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "A funk workout that showcases Prince's command of groove and studio layering, and became a fan favorite for its raw energy." },
        { title: "The Ballad of Dorothy Parker", displayTitle: "The Ballad of Dorothy Parker", duration: "4:03", single: false, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "Named after the American wit Dorothy Parker, this dreamy, deliberately lo-fi track was recorded through faulty studio equipment that Prince chose to keep for its unique sound." },
        { title: "It", displayTitle: "It", duration: "5:09", single: false, explicit: true, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "" },
        { title: "Starfish and Coffee", displayTitle: "Starfish and Coffee", duration: "2:50", single: false, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "A rare children's-style song from Prince, celebrating individuality and tolerance; it has become a staple in elementary music education for its charming simplicity." },
        { title: "Slow Love", displayTitle: "Slow Love", duration: "4:22", single: false, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "" },
        { title: "Hot Thing", displayTitle: "Hot Thing", duration: "5:39", single: true, explicit: true, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "Released as a promotional single, this synth-driven track displays Prince's mastery of late-80s production techniques and his ability to blur funk and electronic dance music." },
        { title: "Forever in My Life", displayTitle: "Forever in My Life", duration: "3:31", single: false, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "" },
        { title: "U Got the Look", displayTitle: "U Got the Look", duration: "3:47", single: true, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "Reaching US #2, this sizzling duet with Sheena Easton was one of the year's biggest pop-rock hits and demonstrated Prince's gift for collaborative chemistry." },
        { title: "If I Was Your Girlfriend", displayTitle: "If I Was Your Girlfriend", duration: "5:00", single: true, explicit: true, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "Recorded under Prince's alter ego Camille (a sped-up vocal persona), this gender-fluid exploration of intimacy has become one of his most critically discussed and progressive compositions." },
        { title: "Strange Relationship", displayTitle: "Strange Relationship", duration: "4:01", single: false, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "" },
        { title: "I Could Never Take the Place of Your Man", displayTitle: "I Could Never Take the Place of Your Man", duration: "6:30", single: true, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "Reaching US #10, this track was originally recorded during the Purple Rain sessions and features a blistering extended guitar solo, one of Prince's finest rock performances." },
        { title: "The Cross", displayTitle: "The Cross", duration: "4:49", single: false, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "A slow-building spiritual rock anthem that closes Disc 2's first half with gospel intensity, reflecting Prince's deep Christian faith." },
        { title: "It's Gonna Be a Beautiful Night", displayTitle: "It's Gonna Be a Beautiful Night", duration: "9:01", single: false, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "Recorded live in Paris with the Revolution, this extended funk jam captures Prince's electrifying stage presence and his band's improvisational skill." },
        { title: "Adore", displayTitle: "Adore", duration: "6:31", single: false, explicit: false, hiddenFromStudentView: false, teacherNote: "The album's closing ballad is widely regarded as one of Prince's most stunning vocal performances, a slow-burning devotional that many critics consider the double album's emotional peak." }
      ],
