      "discussionQuestions": [
          "The album opens with gang violence, crack cocaine, AIDS, and natural disaster — and then moves to dance tracks and love songs. Is that jarring, or does it feel like a deliberate statement? What do you think Prince was saying?",
          "Prince played almost every instrument on this record by himself. Does knowing that change how you hear it? What is lost or gained when one person controls everything?",
          "The album spans funk, rock, ballads, gospel, new wave, and R&B. Does it feel like one coherent album, or a collection of different ideas? Does it matter?",
          "Why do you think Sign 'O' the Times is consistently ranked among the greatest albums ever made, even though it was never Prince's biggest commercial hit?"
      ],
