      "artistYearsActive": "1991 – present",
      "artistOverview": "Portishead are a British musical group from Bristol, England, consisting of singer Beth Gibbons, producer and multi-instrumentalist Geoff Barrow, and guitarist Adrian Utley. Their debut album Dummy essentially invented the genre known as trip-hop, fusing sampled beats, spy-film orchestration, vinyl crackle, and Gibbons's devastatingly raw vocal performances into a sound that was entirely new. The album won the 1995 Mercury Prize and remains one of the most critically admired debut albums in British music history.",
