          "mood": "Raw, desperate, abrasive, vulnerable, cathartic",
          "mainSounds": "Distorted, trebly guitar, Steve Albini's close-miked drum sound, Cobain's voice moving from whisper to scream, angular riffs, cello on 'All Apologies'",
          "productionStyle": "Intentionally lo-fi and confrontational — Steve Albini recorded the band live to two-inch tape at Pachyderm Studio in nine days, deliberately avoiding the polished sheen of Nevermind",
