      "artistOverview": "Nasir Bin Olu Dara Jones — known as Nas — grew up in the Queensbridge Houses in Queens, New York, one of the largest public housing projects in the United States. The son of jazz musician Olu Dara, Nas absorbed music deeply before dropping out of school in eighth grade and channeling his observations of street life into dense, literary rap lyrics. Illmatic, his debut album released when he was just nineteen years old at recording, is widely regarded as one of the greatest hip-hop albums ever made.",
