      "historicalContext": "The Low End Theory arrived in September 1991 — the same month as Nevermind — in a pop landscape being reshaped by multiple revolutions simultaneously. While grunge was exploding on rock radio, hip-hop was splitting between the rising commercial dominance of West Coast gangsta rap and the New York underground's search for new sounds. ATCQ, alongside De La Soul and the Jungle Brothers in the Native Tongues collective, offered a third path: hip-hop rooted in Afrocentric consciousness, jazz music, and a deliberate rejection of street violence as the genre's defining image.",
