      "artistOverview": "Kate Bush is an English singer, songwriter, and producer who burst onto the scene at age 19 with the dramatic hit 'Wuthering Heights.' She was the first woman to have a self-written UK number-one single, and she went on to become one of the most inventive artists in pop music history. Known for her extraordinary vocal range, theatrical storytelling, and refusal to follow trends, Bush has always worked on her own terms — often spending years crafting each album exactly as she imagined it.",
