          "mood": "Dramatic, mysterious, intimate, surreal, sweeping",
          "mainSounds": "Fairlight CMI synthesizer and sampler, layered vocals, orchestral strings, tribal percussion, acoustic piano, processed vocals",
          "productionStyle": "Self-produced at Bush's home studio — meticulous, layered, and cinematic; Side One is polished and radio-ready while Side Two (The Ninth Wave) is a continuous song cycle with sound design and spoken word passages",
          "energy": "Shifts dramatically — from urgent pop hooks to quiet, eerie soundscapes and back to full orchestral climaxes",
          "keyIdea": "The album is split into two distinct halves: five accessible art-pop singles on Side One and a seven-track conceptual song cycle about a woman drowning and clinging to consciousness on Side Two."
