      "artistYearsActive": "1988 – present",
      "artistOverview": "Massive Attack emerged from the Wild Bunch sound system collective in Bristol and created Blue Lines in 1991 — an album so unlike anything that preceded it that critics had to invent a new genre (trip-hop) just to describe it. The group — originally the trio of 3D, Mushroom, and Daddy G — brought hip-hop production techniques, dub bass weights, and orchestral soul samples together with guest vocalists to build something that felt simultaneously futuristic and ancient. They remain one of the most influential British acts of the past thirty years.",
