      "artistYearsActive": "1976 – 1980, 1985 – 1990, 2000 – present",
      "artistOverview": "Wire formed in London in 1976 as a punk band and then immediately began questioning what punk meant. While their contemporaries were adding guitar solos and anthemic choruses, Wire were stripping those things away — removing anything they considered unnecessary until only the essential remained. Pink Flag (1977) is the most extreme expression of that philosophy: 21 tracks in under 36 minutes, most barely over a minute long, several under 30 seconds. The band went on to further reinvent themselves with each subsequent album and are considered one of the founding groups of post-punk, new wave, and indie rock.",
