      "artistYearsActive": "1975 – 1991",
      "artistOverview": "Talking Heads formed at the Rhode Island School of Design in 1975 and became one of the central acts of the New York new wave scene. Singer and guitarist David Byrne, bassist Tina Weymouth, drummer Chris Frantz, and keyboardist Jerry Harrison made four albums that progressively absorbed more experimental and global influences, culminating in Remain in Light. Working with producer Brian Eno, they built the album from African polyrhythms and studio layering rather than conventional songwriting, and created something that had never existed before: American art-rock filtered through Fela Kuti. The album is their undisputed masterpiece and one of the most analysed records in rock history.",
