      "artistOverview": "Radiohead formed in Abingdon, Oxfordshire in 1985 and spent their early years as a guitar-driven alternative rock band. The Bends was the moment they stopped sounding like everyone else — Thom Yorke's voice became something extraordinary, the guitars expanded into cathedrals of sound, and the emotional intensity found a shape that matched it. OK Computer and Kid A would make them one of the most important bands of the era, but The Bends is the album where they first showed what they were capable of.",
