      "artistOverview": "The Pixies formed in Boston in 1986 and invented a structural vocabulary that alternative rock has been borrowing from ever since: the quiet verse that explodes into a distorted, screaming chorus. Black Francis (Charles Thompson) wrote surrealist, often violent imagery over pop melodies; Kim Deal's bass locked the songs together with a cool authority the chaos needed. Surfer Rosa was their first full LP, recorded in two weeks with Steve Albini, and it remains one of the rawest and most exciting records of the alternative rock era.",
