      "discussionQuestions": [
          "'Where Is My Mind?' was ignored in 1988 and became famous in 1999. What does that tell us about how songs find their audiences — and whether a song's meaning can change over time?",
          "Steve Albini recorded this album with almost no reverb, no polish, and no attempt to make it sound commercial. Do you think that was the right decision? Would the album be better or worse with a more conventional production?",
          "Kurt Cobain said he was trying to write a Pixies song when he wrote 'Smells Like Teen Spirit.' What does it mean when one of the biggest rock songs in history is openly an imitation of a different band?",
          "Doolittle (1989) is already in our library — it was Surfer Rosa refined and slightly more accessible. Which version of the Pixies do you think is more interesting, and why?"
      ],
