      "importance": [
          "Widely considered the album that permanently established Atlanta as the creative center of hip-hop — not an imitation of New York, but its own world with its own rules.",
          "André 3000's verse on 'Return of the 'G'' and 'Da Art of Storytellin' Part 1' are considered among the finest rap writing of the 1990s.",
          "The album's blend of live instrumentation, neo-soul, and hip-hop directly influenced the genre boundary-crossing that defines contemporary Black American music.",
          "Rolling Stone ranks Aquemini among the 500 Greatest Albums of All Time; it is consistently cited as Outkast's creative peak even by those who consider Speakerboxxx/The Love Below their commercial peak."
      ],
      "historicalContext": "Aquemini was released in September 1998, at a moment when hip-hop's commercial center was firmly in New York and Los Angeles. Atlanta had been producing important rap music for years, but it wasn't taken as seriously by coastal critics and industry figures. Aquemini was the album that made that coastal dismissal impossible to sustain — it was simply too ambitious, too original, and too good to be explained away. Within a few years, Atlanta would be the undisputed center of American hip-hop.",
