      "keySongs": [
          {
              "title": "Aquemini",
              "note": "Listen to how different André and Big Boi sound back-to-back. What do their voices communicate before you even process the words? The album title is the combination of their star signs — this is the song that explains why that matters."
          },
          {
              "title": "Da Art of Storytellin' (Part 1)",
              "note": "Both MCs tell a story about a real person from a specific moment. What does specificity do to a rap lyric — how is a story about one real person different from a general observation?"
          },
          {
              "title": "SpottieOttieDopaliscious",
              "note": "Six and a half minutes — a long jazz-funk intro before the verses begin. Most rap tracks don't work this way. What does the musical introduction do for the mood by the time the MCs start rapping?"
          },
          {
              "title": "Liberation",
              "note": "Eight minutes, meditative, with Erykah Badu. This is how the album ends — not with energy, but with something like peace. Why do you think they chose this as the closing statement?"
          }
      ],
