      "artistOverview": "Elliott Smith was an American singer-songwriter and multi-instrumentalist based primarily in Portland, Oregon. Known for his fingerpicked acoustic guitar style, his close-mic'd intimate vocal delivery, and his ability to describe depression, addiction, and self-doubt with extraordinary lyrical precision, Smith recorded several albums of increasing complexity before his work reached a mass audience through the Good Will Hunting soundtrack in 1997. He died in 2003. The music itself — quiet, beautiful, and unflinching — remains among the most beloved in American indie folk.",
