      "artistOverview": "Sly & The Family Stone were one of the most radical bands in American music history — a racially and gender-integrated group from the San Francisco Bay Area who fused rock, funk, soul, and psychedelia into something that had never existed before. Their 1969 album Stand! was the sound of utopian optimism. There's a Riot Goin' On, released just two years later, is its dark mirror: recorded almost entirely alone by Sly Stone in a home studio, it documents the collapse of that vision under the weight of addiction, commercial pressure, and a changing political climate.",
