      "discussionQuestions": [
          "Dylan's fans booed him when he went electric — they felt he had betrayed the folk movement that made him famous. Was that a reasonable reaction, or do artists owe their audiences nothing except honesty?",
          "Side 1 is electric rock; Side 2 is acoustic folk — on the same album. Which side do you think sounds more 'like Dylan'? Is there a right answer?",
          "This album came out the same month as the Selma-to-Montgomery marches. Dylan's previous albums were anthems for civil rights. Why might a protest singer choose this moment to turn away from political songwriting?",
          "'Subterranean Homesick Blues' is often called a precursor to rap. After listening to it — do you hear that? What would have to change to make it a hip-hop track?"
      ],
