      "artistYearsActive": "1980 – present",
      "artistOverview": "New Order formed in Manchester in 1980 from the ruins of Joy Division after their lead singer Ian Curtis died by suicide on the eve of the band's first American tour. Rather than replace Curtis, the remaining three members — Bernard Sumner, Peter Hook, and Stephen Morris — recruited keyboardist Gillian Gilbert and began again with a new name and a radical new direction. Where Joy Division was dark and guitar-driven, New Order embraced synthesizers, drum machines, and the emerging electronic dance music they heard in New York and Chicago clubs. Power, Corruption & Lies was the album that defined their new identity — and the era.",
