      "artistOverview": "Kanye West grew up in Chicago and first made his name as a producer, crafting hits for Jay-Z and others before forcing his way into rap as a solo artist. His first three albums established him as hip-hop's most ambitious pop experimentalist. After a series of personal and public crises — including his mother's death in 2007 and the Taylor Swift VMA incident in 2009 — he retreated to Hawaii with a rotating cast of collaborators and made My Beautiful Dark Twisted Fantasy, widely regarded as his masterwork: a maximalist, confessional, and sonically overwhelming portrait of fame, ego, and self-destruction.",
