              "teacherNote": "Samples Smokey Robinson's 'Will You Love Me Tomorrow' — a lush, gorgeous production underpins lyrics about a destructive relationship. Rick Ross's verse at the end is among his best recorded work. One of the album's most soulful, emotional moments."
