      "discussionQuestions": [
          "Kanye made this album after being publicly humiliated worldwide. The album is partly a confession and partly a defence. Does the context of how it was made change how you hear it — or should a piece of art be judged purely on its own terms?",
          "The production on this album is intentionally overwhelming — dozens of layers, famous guests on every track, samples from rock, soul, folk, and electronic music. Is there a point where ambition becomes too much? Does maximalism work here or does it get in the way?",
          "Nicki Minaj's verse on 'Monster' is one of the most discussed guest performances in hip-hop history. What makes a guest verse memorable — is it technical skill, personality, surprise, or something else?",
          "The album ends with Gil Scott-Heron — a 70-year-old poet and activist — delivering a 1970 protest poem. What does that choice say about what Kanye was trying to do with this album? Is he putting his own story in a larger historical context, or is he borrowing someone else's credibility?"
      ],
