      "artistYearsActive": "2001 – present",
      "artistOverview": "Arcade Fire formed in Montreal, Quebec, in 2001 around husband-and-wife duo Win Butler and Régine Chassagne. The band quickly expanded into a large collective of multi-instrumentalists, typically performing with seven or more members on stage and switching instruments between songs. Funeral, their debut album, was written and recorded during a period when several band members suffered bereavements in their families — the title reflects that. It was released on Merge Records to immediate critical attention, and within a year had become one of the most celebrated debut albums of the decade, largely through word-of-mouth in an era before social media had the power to do that work artificially.",
