              "hiddenFromStudentView": false,
              "teacherNote": "Named after Laïka, the Soviet space dog sent into orbit in 1957 with no way to return. The song's energy is anxious and propulsive — a garage-rock burst after the opener's delicacy. The title animal, sent to die, becomes a symbol for sacrifice and abandonment."
