      "discussionQuestions": [
          "Several band members were actually grieving when they made this album. Does knowing that change how you hear it? Can you tell the difference between music made during real grief and music that just describes grief?",
          "'Wake Up' became famous partly because it was in a video game and a movie trailer — reaching people who had never heard of Arcade Fire. Is that a valid way for music to find its audience, or does that kind of exposure cheapen the song?",
          "The band has seven or more members and most of them switch instruments between songs. Why would a band choose to work that way? What does that communal, collective approach do to the sound — and to the live experience?",
          "Funeral was one of the last albums to become a phenomenon through word-of-mouth alone, before social media existed. Do you think it would have had the same impact if it had been released today, with TikTok and streaming algorithms? What would be different?"
      ],
