      "artistYearsActive": "1977 – present",
      "artistOverview": "Björk Guðmundsdóttir was born in Reykjavík in 1965 and released her first solo album at age eleven. She spent her early career in a series of bands, including the post-punk group the Sugarcubes, before moving to London and making Debut at 27. Produced largely by Nellee Hooper — who had worked with Soul II Soul and Massive Attack — Debut placed her orchestral, technically astounding voice over electronic and dance production in a way that had no precedent. She has released nine solo albums since, each radically different from the last, making her one of the most restlessly experimental figures in popular music. She is also a significant visual artist, filmmaker, and curator.",
