      "artistOverview": "R.E.M. formed in Athens, Georgia in 1980 and spent the 1980s as the defining American alternative rock band, pioneering jangly guitar-driven college rock before signing to a major label and achieving arena-level fame. By 1992 they were one of the biggest bands in the world — yet instead of doubling down on the anthemic rock of their breakthrough Out of Time, they made Automatic for the People: a hushed, orchestrated meditation on loss, mortality, and the passage of time. It remains one of the most surprising pivots in rock history.",
