      "historicalContext": "Released in October 1992, Automatic arrived at a moment of unusual cultural heaviness: AIDS, recession, a generation of young people dealing with mortality earlier than expected. R.E.M. had just broken through to arena scale with Out of Time (1991) — they could have repeated the formula. Instead they stripped back to acoustic instruments and strings, writing an album saturated with grief and memory. Its restraint felt radical next to the loud, distorted alternative rock dominating radio that same year.",
