      "artistOverview": "Joni Mitchell is one of the most important and technically sophisticated songwriters of the twentieth century. Born in Alberta, Canada, she emerged from the folk scene of the 1960s and spent the early 1970s making increasingly adventurous records. Blue (1971) is often called the greatest singer-songwriter album ever made — yet Mitchell's response was not to repeat it but to push further into jazz harmony and pop orchestration. Court and Spark (1974) was the result: her most commercially successful album, her most musically complex, and by many accounts her finest hour.",
