      "artistOverview": "Bruce Springsteen grew up in Freehold, New Jersey, and became one of the defining figures of American rock music with his E Street Band. Known for marathon live performances and anthemic stadium rock, he surprised everyone in 1982 by releasing Nebraska — an album recorded alone on a home cassette machine, with no band, no overdubs, and no polish. The contrast with Born to Run (1975), his best-known work, is one of the most dramatic artistic pivots in rock history.",
