      "historicalContext": "Nebraska was released in September 1982, at the depths of a severe US recession. Unemployment had reached 10.8% — the highest since the Great Depression. Ronald Reagan's economic policies were gutting the industrial Midwest and working-class communities that Springsteen grew up in. While arena rock and synth-pop dominated radio, Springsteen made an album that sounded like a field recording from the places no one was singing about.",
