      "artistOverview": "GZA (Gary Grice) is a founding member of the Wu-Tang Clan and widely considered the group's most skilled lyricist — known for dense, precise rhymes with fewer words used to greater effect than almost any MC of his era. Born in Brooklyn and raised partly in Staten Island, he had already released a shelved debut album before Wu-Tang broke through. Liquid Swords, produced entirely by RZA, is considered his masterwork and one of the defining solo records of the Wu-Tang collective's golden period.",
