      "discussionQuestions": [
          "Sufjan announced a fifty-state project and completed two albums. Is an ambitious project that fails to be completed still valuable — or does the incompleteness undermine it?",
          "'John Wayne Gacy, Jr.' ends by implicating the narrator in human evil. What do you think Sufjan means by that final turn? Is it honest or is it self-indulgent?",
          "Illinois is 74 minutes long with 22 tracks and dozens of instruments. Is more ambition always better in art — or can an album be too big?",
          "'Chicago' is about going home but also about having made mistakes. Have you ever felt the urge to go back somewhere — a place, a time, a person — knowing it wouldn't be the same?"
      ],
