      "artistOverview": "The National formed in Cincinnati, Ohio, in 1999 and relocated to Brooklyn, New York, before recording their breakthrough albums. The band consists of vocalist Matt Berninger and two pairs of brothers: Aaron and Bryce Dessner (guitar) and Scott and Bryan Devendorf (bass and drums). Their sound combines Berninger's deep baritone — which draws comparisons to Leonard Cohen and Nick Cave — with dense orchestral arrangements and lyrics about anxiety, aspiration, and the gap between who we are and who we thought we would be.",
