      "artistYearsActive": "1983 – present",
      "artistOverview": "Guided by Voices is a band from Dayton, Ohio, built around prolific songwriter Robert Pollard, a former 4th-grade elementary school teacher who spent years recording songs on a 4-track cassette machine in his basement while holding down his day job. The band released albums for years in near-total obscurity before Bee Thousand broke through to critical acclaim in 1994, when Pollard was 37 years old. GBV are famous for their extremely short songs, their embrace of lo-fi tape hiss as an aesthetic, and Pollard's seemingly inexhaustible gift for melody — the band has released over 30 studio albums.",
