          "mood": "Restless, tender, defiant, self-aware, bittersweet",
          "mainSounds": "Electric guitars (Bob Stinson's distinctive lead work), Westerberg's weathered vocals, tight rhythm section, occasional piano and organ, more polished production than their indie records but still rough at the edges",
          "productionStyle": "Produced by Tommy Erdelyi (the original drummer of The Ramones, credited as Tommy Ramone) — cleaner and more radio-ready than their Twin/Tone records, but the band's essential roughness was not smoothed away entirely",
          "energy": "Alternates between driven, riff-based rockers and genuinely vulnerable mid-tempo songs — Westerberg could write a drinking anthem and a heartbreaker back to back",
          "keyIdea": "Tim is a band in conflict with itself — trying to make a major-label album while making clear at every turn that they resented what a major-label album was supposed to be."
