          "mainSounds": "Overdriven guitars pushed into distortion and feedback, John Cale's viola treated as a noise instrument, Maureen Tucker's minimalist drumming (she played standing up, hitting downward), Lou Reed's deadpan vocals — and on 'Sister Ray,' everything simultaneously at maximum volume for 17 minutes",
