      "artistOverview": "The Who formed in London in 1964 and became one of the defining bands of the British rock scene. Pete Townshend (guitar, principal songwriter), Roger Daltrey (lead vocals), John Entwistle (bass), and Keith Moon (drums) were known for their explosive live performances — Townshend smashing guitars, Moon destroying drum kits. The Who Sell Out (1967) is their third album and their most conceptually inventive. Their next album, Tommy (1969), was rock's first opera. Keith Moon died in 1978; John Entwistle in 2002. The surviving members continue to perform.",
