      "artistOverview": "Funkadelic was the rock-oriented project of George Clinton's Parliament-Funkadelic collective, which also included the more straightforwardly funk-oriented Parliament. Clinton assembled a large rotating collective of musicians in Detroit and later in Plainfield, New Jersey. Where Parliament was defined by its bass-heavy groove and horns, Funkadelic was guitar-led and psychedelic — deeply influenced by Jimi Hendrix and Sly Stone. Maggot Brain (1971) is their third album and widely considered their peak achievement. The collective has continued in various forms under Clinton's leadership to the present day.",
