      "artistYearsActive": "1956 – 1999",
      "artistOverview": "Curtis Mayfield was one of the most important figures in soul music — first as a founding member of The Impressions, then as a solo artist and producer. His music combined deeply grooved funk and lush orchestral arrangements with a social conscience shaped by the civil rights movement. Superfly, his soundtrack to Gordon Parks Jr.'s 1972 film, is widely considered his masterpiece: a set of songs that operate as moral commentary on the drug trade, drug addiction, and ghetto life, written from the inside with compassion rather than condemnation.",
