          "mainSounds": "Wah-wah guitar, lush string arrangements, layered percussion, Mayfield's signature falsetto vocals",
          "productionStyle": "Richly orchestrated but rhythmically tight — the strings and horns create a cinematic sweep while the rhythm section keeps everything grounded in the street",
          "energy": "Mid-tempo and hypnotic throughout — the groove pulls you in while the lyrics make you uncomfortable",
          "keyIdea": "Mayfield wrote songs that sound seductive on the surface and read as warnings underneath — the tension between those two things is the whole point."
