      "artistOverview": "Brian Eno began his career as the synthesizer player and 'non-musician' in Roxy Music before leaving to pursue a solo career defined by experiment and concept. He is one of the most influential figures in twentieth-century music — not for chart success but for inventing entire ways of thinking about sound. Another Green World is the album where his two impulses (pop songwriting and pure sound texture) balanced most perfectly. He later developed the ambient ideas here into his Ambient series and became one of the most sought-after producers in rock, working with David Bowie, Talking Heads, U2, and Coldplay.",
