      "discussionQuestions": [
          "Some tracks on this album have no melody, no lyrics, and no traditional structure. Is that still a song? Where do you draw the line between music and sound?",
          "Eno used a deck of instruction cards to make compositional decisions. Does knowing that change how you hear the music — does it feel less 'real' somehow, or does it not matter how the music was made?",
          "The album is half vocal songs, half pure texture. Which half did you respond to more? Did the two halves feel like they belonged on the same record?",
          "Eno later produced David Bowie's Berlin Trilogy and U2's The Joshua Tree using similar ideas. Listen to 'Where the Streets Have No Name' with this album in mind — can you hear Eno's fingerprints on it?"
      ],
