      "artistYearsActive": "1977 – 1984, 2004–2011, 2019 – present",
      "artistOverview": "Gang of Four formed at Leeds University in 1977, where the members were studying fine art and English literature. Their music applied Marxist and post-structuralist theory — ideas about consumerism, alienation, desire, and power — to a stripped-down post-punk sound that borrowed heavily from funk. Entertainment! is their debut and their most celebrated album: a record that sounds both confrontational and irresistibly physical. Andy Gill's staccato, percussive guitar style and Dave Allen's locked-in bass created a template copied by nearly every angular guitar band that followed.",
