          "genre": "Post-Punk / Funk-Punk",
          "mood": "Angular, urgent, tense, danceable, politically uncomfortable",
          "mainSounds": "Staccato stabbing guitar (Andy Gill's signature percussive style), locked funk bass, minimal drums, shouted/half-spoken vocals, deliberate empty space in the mix",
          "productionStyle": "Stripped down to the essentials — no reverb, no overdubs, no softening. The gaps between the notes are as important as the notes themselves.",
          "energy": "High tension throughout — the music is physically exciting and intellectually demanding at the same time",
          "keyIdea": "Gang of Four believed the way music sounds is itself a political statement — clean, sparse, rhythm-first, no comfort, no decoration."
