      "artistYearsActive": "1968 – 2017",
      "artistOverview": "Black Sabbath formed in Birmingham, England in 1968 — four working-class teenagers from one of Britain's most industrial cities. They were not attempting to invent a genre; they were attempting to make music that felt as heavy and dark as the world they grew up in. Guitarist Tony Iommi lost the tips of two fingers on his right hand in a factory accident at age 17. Unable to play in standard tuning, he devised a lower tuning and lighter string gauges to make playing bearable. That accident created the low, crushing sound that defines heavy metal. Master of Reality is their third album and, to many listeners, the heaviest record they ever made.",
