      "artistOverview": "Minutemen were a trio from San Pedro, California — a working-class port town near Los Angeles. D. Boon, Mike Watt, and George Hurley grew up together, taught themselves to play, and built a sound unlike anything else in punk: short, angular songs that mixed hardcore speed with jazz rhythms, folk-punk lyricism, and relentless political commentary. They recorded prolifically for SST Records and toured constantly in a van, living by the ethos 'we jam econo.' The band ended tragically when D. Boon died in a van accident in December 1985 at age 27.",
