      "discussionQuestions": [
          "The Minutemen believed music should be cheap to make and cheap to attend so any working-class kid could participate. Does that philosophy change how you think about the music industry today?",
          "'History Lesson — Part II' is about how two friends became musicians by sharing records and ideas. Do you have something in your life — a book, a game, a song — that you first discovered through a friend and that changed what you were interested in?",
          "Most of these songs are under two minutes. Does length matter to you when you listen to music? What can a two-minute song do that a five-minute song can't — and vice versa?",
          "D. Boon died at 27 and the band immediately dissolved. Does knowing a band ended tragically and suddenly change how you hear the music they left behind?"
      ],
