      "artistOverview": "Hüsker Dü were a trio from Minneapolis, Minnesota — Bob Mould on guitar and vocals, Greg Norton on bass, and Grant Hart on drums and vocals. They started as a straightforward hardcore band before developing a sound that merged the speed and aggression of punk with pop melodies, minor-key introspection, and conceptual ambition. Their two SST albums — Zen Arcade and Flip Your Wig — and their subsequent major-label debut Candy Apple Grey laid the groundwork for virtually every American alternative band of the 1990s. They broke up in 1988 under the weight of internal tensions.",
