      "classroomSafeMode": true,
      "keyFacts": [
          "The entire double album — 23 tracks, over 65 minutes — was recorded in less than 40 hours over a single weekend in 1984, making it one of the fastest double albums ever made.",
          "Side four closes with 'Reoccurring Dreams,' a 14-minute ambient instrumental that is entirely unlike the preceding 22 tracks — it represents, within the album's concept, the protagonist's final retreat into inner life.",
          "Grant Hart and Bob Mould wrote all the songs separately and alternated them across the album — their contrasting sensibilities (Hart: melodic, Hart: warmer; Mould: abrasive, dense) create the internal tension that makes the record feel larger than either songwriter alone.",
          "A 33⅓ book dedicated to Zen Arcade was written by Matthew Fritch, tracing the album's recording, its conceptual structure, and its long influence on alternative rock."
      ],
