      "discussionQuestions": [
          "The album was recorded in less than 40 hours. Does knowing that change how you hear it — does it feel rushed, or does the urgency feel right for the subject matter?",
          "'Pink Turns to Blue' is a song about a drug overdose, and it's one of the album's most melodically beautiful tracks. Does it feel wrong to make something beautiful about something tragic — or does that contradiction make it more powerful?",
          "Bob Mould and Grant Hart wrote completely separately — you can hear the difference between their approaches. Is that contrast between two distinct voices inside one band a strength or a tension? Does it matter?",
          "The album closes with 14 minutes of silence and drift, after 22 tracks of furious punk. Why do you think they ended the record that way, and does it change what came before it?"
      ],
