      "artistOverview": "Prince Rogers Nelson was a singer, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, and producer from Minneapolis, Minnesota. He played virtually every instrument on his recordings, produced himself from the beginning of his career, and refused to be classified by genre, race, or expectation. Purple Rain — simultaneously a film, an album, and a commercial phenomenon — arrived when he was 26 years old and made him the most celebrated musician in America. He remained one of the most creatively prolific and fiercely independent artists in pop history until his death in April 2016.",
