      "discussionQuestions": [
          "'When Doves Cry' removed the bass line and went to #1 for four weeks. What does that tell us about the relationship between rule-breaking and commercial success — is it always a risk to do something unusual, or does unusual sometimes become exactly what people want?",
          "The Parental Advisory sticker exists because of this album. Do you think warning labels on music are useful, harmful, or irrelevant in the age of streaming? Has knowing a record has explicit content ever changed whether you listened to it?",
          "Purple Rain was simultaneously a film and an album — it was designed to be experienced both ways. Does knowing a piece of music was made for a visual context change how you hear it?",
          "Prince was biracial and routinely rejected the idea that he made Black music, White music, rock, R&B, or any single category. Does the genre fluency on this album feel like freedom or does it feel like something else — ambiguity, restlessness, something you can't easily name?"
      ],
