      "artistYearsActive": "1983 – 1999, 2007 – present",
      "artistOverview": "The Jesus and Mary Chain were formed in East Kilbride, Scotland by brothers Jim and William Reid. Relocating to London, they became notorious almost immediately — their early shows were often 15 to 20 minutes long before the band walked off stage, frequently to jeering crowds and actual riots. Their debut album Psychocandy arrived in late 1985 and introduced a sound that almost nobody had heard before: classic 1960s pop melodies filtered through violent amounts of guitar feedback and distortion. It was barely noticed at the time, but it became one of the most cited debut albums in alternative music history.",
