      "keySongs": [
          {
              "title": "One More Hour",
              "note": "The best entry point for Corin Tucker's voice — that vibrato is unlike anything else in rock. The song is ostensibly a breakup song, but listen to how Tucker's delivery transforms sadness into something that sounds closer to power. Does the vocal style change the emotional meaning?"
          },
          {
              "title": "Words and Guitar",
              "note": "A song that explains the band's entire position in one lyric: music as a tool, as a weapon, as a place to belong. Listen for how the guitar and vocal relate — do they say the same thing, or does the guitar argue with the lyric?"
          },
          {
              "title": "Dig Me Out",
              "note": "The opener sets the pace for everything that follows. Janet Weiss's drums come in first — listen to how the entire song is built around her. Without a bassist, the drummer becomes the anchor. Can you hear the two guitars dividing the rhythmic and melodic roles that one guitar and one bass would normally share?"
          },
          {
              "title": "Jenny",
              "note": "The moment the album steps back from aggression into something more open. Compare the production on this track to the opener — same album, very different emotional register. What does the contrast tell you about what the band is trying to do across the whole record?"
          }
      ],
