      "discussionQuestions": [
          "Sleater-Kinney came out of a movement that said women's voices and experiences were being left out of rock music. Listening to Dig Me Out — do you think they were right? Does the music itself make that argument, or just the context around it?",
          "The band uses two guitars and no bass. Most rock bands don't do this. Why do you think the bass exists in most rock music — and what does it change to remove it?",
          "Carrie Brownstein later became famous as a comedian and actress on Portlandia. What does it mean for an artist to succeed in a completely different field? Does it change how you think about the music?",
          "We've now heard hip-hop (Paid in Full) and guitar-based feminist rock (Dig Me Out) in consecutive weeks. Both came out of genres that felt like they had something to prove. What do the two albums have in common beyond that?"
      ],
