    "artistOverview": "Bruce Springsteen, known as 'The Boss,' is a rock singer-songwriter from New Jersey who has been making music since the late 1960s. He is known for long, energetic live shows — sometimes over three hours — and for writing songs about working-class American life: factory workers, Vietnam veterans, people whose American Dream hasn't quite arrived. Born in the U.S.A. made him one of the biggest-selling artists in the world while also being his most politically misunderstood record.",
