        "productionStyle": "Big and polished — synthesizers dominate the early 1980s sound; drums are enormous; the production is arena-ready but the lyrics are intimate.",
        "energy": "High and anthemic throughout — designed to fill stadiums while telling stories about people who can't afford the ticket.",
        "keyIdea": "Born in the U.S.A. is a protest record wearing a party costume — the gap between the triumphant sound and the critical lyrics is the whole point."
