    "discussionQuestions": [
        "Ronald Reagan's campaign used the title track as a patriotic anthem without Springsteen's permission. Who owns the meaning of a song once it's released — the artist or the audience?",
        "The album sold 30 million copies and produced seven Top 10 singles. Does massive commercial success make it harder to take a record seriously as social commentary?",
        "Compare the music of 'Born in the U.S.A.' to its lyrics. Can a song's sound and its meaning be completely contradictory — and can that contradiction be intentional?",
        "My Hometown ends the album on a note of uncertainty and decline. Is that an appropriate ending for a record that became the soundtrack to 1980s American optimism?"
    ],
