    "artistOverview": "Aretha Franklin is widely considered the greatest singer in American music history. Born in Memphis and raised in Detroit, she grew up singing in church — her father, Reverend C.L. Franklin, was one of the most celebrated Baptist ministers in America. By the time she signed to Atlantic Records in 1966, she had been singing professionally for years, but it was the Atlantic era that made her a legend. Songs like 'Respect,' 'Chain of Fools,' and 'Think' defined soul music in the late 1960s. Amazing Grace was her conscious return to the gospel tradition that made her who she was.",
