    "artistOverview": "Blondie were a New York band who emerged from the same CBGB punk scene as the Ramones and Television but had their eyes fixed firmly on pop radio. Singer Debbie Harry had trained as a waitress, a Playboy Bunny, and a singer in a folk group before becoming one of the defining faces of new wave. Blondie's secret was that they genuinely loved trash culture, girl-group pop, disco, and reggae as much as they loved punk — and they weren't embarrassed about any of it. Parallel Lines made them international stars by leaning into all of those influences at once.",
