        "genre": "New Wave / Power Pop / Pop Punk",
        "mood": "Cool, playful, seductive, ironic, energetic",
        "mainSounds": "Keyboards, punchy rhythm guitar, driving drums, Debbie Harry's deadpan-to-soaring vocals, disco-influenced bass lines",
        "productionStyle": "Crisp, polished, radio-ready — producer Mike Chapman came from glam rock and brought commercial instincts to CBGB's rougher aesthetic.",
        "energy": "Consistently high but varied — moves between pure punk pace, disco groove, and mid-tempo pop effortlessly.",
        "keyIdea": "Parallel Lines is a record that contains multitudes — punk, pop, disco, girl-group soul — without apologizing for any of it, and the result sounds more modern today than almost anything from its era."
