    "discussionQuestions": [
        "'Heart of Glass' was a disco song from a punk band, and it made many fans angry. Is genre loyalty a meaningful thing, or is it just tribalism? Can a band belong to two scenes at once?",
        "Debbie Harry was one of very few women at the center of the late-1970s New York punk scene. How did she navigate being a female frontwoman in that environment — and does the music reflect that position?",
        "Parallel Lines was produced by Mike Chapman, who came from glam rock — not punk. How much credit does the producer deserve for a record, versus the artist who wrote and performed it?",
        "The album mixes punk, pop, disco, reggae, and art rock in twelve tracks. Is that range a strength — proof of Blondie's versatility — or does it prevent the album from having a clear identity?"
    ],
