        "Rick Rubin — who had produced Run-DMC, the Beastie Boys, and Slayer — signed Cash to his label and recorded him alone at home with an acoustic guitar. No band, no studio, no production.",
        "Many of the songs on this album are covers — Cash chose material from folk tradition, from contemporary singer-songwriters, and from gospel, performing each as if he had always known it.",
        "The album was initially ignored by country radio but embraced by rock critics and alternative music audiences, eventually winning Cash a Grammy and introducing him to an entirely new generation of listeners."
