    "discussionQuestions": [
        "Rick Rubin made almost no production choices on this album — his main decision was to take everything away. Is that a valid form of production?",
        "Cash covers songs by Tom Waits, Nick Lowe, Leonard Cohen, and Glenn Danzig. How does his voice change what those songs mean?",
        "This album was ignored by country radio but embraced by rock critics. What does that tell us about genre boundaries and who 'owns' an artist?",
        "Cash was 62 years old and considered finished. This album relaunched his career. What does this album suggest about aging, authenticity, and what we expect from artists over time?"
    ],
