    "artistOverview": "Kraftwerk are a German electronic music group formed in Düsseldorf in 1970 by Ralf Hütter and Florian Schneider. They replaced traditional rock instruments with synthesizers, drum machines, and vocoders, and presented themselves as man-machine hybrids — performing behind banks of electronics with identical haircuts and suits. Their influence on electronic music, hip-hop, synth-pop, techno, and dance music is almost impossible to overstate. Computer World, released in 1981, predicted networked computing, surveillance culture, digital communication, and the smartphone era with eerie accuracy.",
