    "discussionQuestions": [
        "Kraftwerk described the internet, networked computing, digital surveillance, and online loneliness in 1981. What does it feel like to hear those predictions now that they've come true?",
        "Every sound on this album is made by a machine. Does that make it feel less human to you — or does the emotion in 'Computer Love' prove that machines can express something human?",
        "Kraftwerk's 'Numbers' was sampled by Afrika Bambaataa to create electro and hip-hop's electronic sound. What does it mean for one genre to grow directly out of another one?",
        "The album presents surveillance — Interpol, FBI, Deutsche Bank — in a completely calm, non-judgmental way. Is Kraftwerk criticizing that world, celebrating it, or just describing it?"
    ],
