    "classroomSafeMode": false,
    "keyFacts": [
        "Rid of Me was produced by Steve Albini — best known for Nirvana's In Utero — recorded live to tape with no overdubs, no reverb, and no compression, giving the album its famously exposed, uncomfortable sound.",
        "PJ Harvey was 23 years old and played most of the instruments herself; the album was recorded in ten days at Pachyderm Studio in Minnesota.",
        "The album's approach to female anger and sexuality was deliberately confrontational — Harvey has said she was uninterested in being liked, only in being honest.",
        "A 33⅓ book on Rid of Me was written by Kate Schatz, examining what the album says about women, aggression, and the boundaries of what rock music is allowed to sound like."
    ],
