    "artistOverview": "Michael Jackson was an American singer, songwriter, and dancer from Gary, Indiana, who became one of the most famous and commercially successful entertainers in history. He began performing as a child with his brothers in The Jackson 5 and launched a solo career that produced some of the best-selling albums of all time, including Thriller (1982), which remains the best-selling album in history. Jackson was known for his extraordinary dancing — including the moonwalk — his visual ambition in music videos, and his ability to synthesise virtually every strand of Black American music into a global pop sound.",
