    "keySongs": [
        {
            "title": "Accordion",
            "note": "The album really starts here — DOOM introduces himself as a villain over a sample of an actual accordion. Listen for how many rhymes he packs into each line. Is it easy to follow, or does it take multiple listens to catch everything?"
        },
        {
            "title": "All Caps",
            "note": "Built around a 1964 jazz sample, the hook tells you to write his name in all capital letters. The instruction is part joke, part genuine demand for respect. What does it say about an artist when they tell you exactly how to refer to them?"
        },
        {
            "title": "Figaro",
            "note": "One of the album's most beautiful-sounding beats — Madlib's sample gives the track a warmth that's unusual for this album. Does the contrast between the beat's beauty and DOOM's deadpan delivery create tension, or do they complement each other?"
        },
        {
            "title": "Fancy Clown",
            "note": "DOOM raps as Viktor Vaughn — a different character from his own universe — about MF DOOM. One persona is commenting on another persona. How far can you take the idea of a constructed artistic identity before it stops being meaningful and becomes just a game?"
        }
    ],
