    "artistOverview": "A Tribe Called Quest were a hip-hop group from Queens, New York, formed by Q-Tip, Phife Dawg, Ali Shaheed Muhammad, and Jarobi White. They became central figures in the Native Tongues collective — a loose movement of groups who rejected gangsta rap's aggression in favor of Afrocentric consciousness, playful wordplay, and jazz-based production. Their records combined warm sample-driven beats with lyrics that were simultaneously street-smart and intellectually curious, making them one of the most influential groups in hip-hop history.",
