    "historicalContext": "People's Instinctive Travels arrived in November 1990, at a moment when hip-hop was splitting in two directions: West Coast gangsta rap growing louder and more confrontational, and an East Coast alternative scene reaching for something different. ATCQ's debut landed in that space — Queens kids sampling jazz, writing about girls and food and everyday life, choosing curiosity over toughness. It didn't chart massively on release but became the foundational text for every hip-hop artist who later chose sophistication over aggression.",
