    "artistOverview": "Dinosaur Jr. formed in Amherst, Massachusetts in 1984 around guitarist J Mascis, whose approach to the electric guitar — loud, melodic, simultaneously shredding and melancholic — became one of the most influential sounds in alternative rock. Despite being a band, Mascis recorded nearly all of You're Living All Over Me himself, playing guitar, bass, and drums. Bassist Lou Barlow was eventually fired and went on to form Sebadoh; Murph played drums on tour. Their combination of Neil Young-influenced guitar heroics and underground punk attitude created the sonic DNA for the next decade of American alternative music.",
