    "artistYearsActive": "1971 – 1974, 1993 – 2010",
    "artistOverview": "Big Star formed in Memphis, Tennessee in 1971 around Alex Chilton — a teenager who had already scored a number-one hit with The Box Tops in 1967 — and guitarist Chris Bell. Their first album, #1 Record, went almost unheard due to catastrophic distribution failures. By Radio City, Bell had left the band, and Chilton was effectively running the project alone. Despite the commercial failure of both records, Big Star became one of the most cited influences in indie and alternative rock — R.E.M., The Replacements, Teenage Fanclub, and Elliott Smith all pointed directly at them as formative.",
