    "artistOverview": "Elvis Costello (born Declan MacManus) emerged from London's pub rock scene in 1977 and immediately distinguished himself with a ferocious intelligence and an almost uncomfortable lyrical density. In the span of three years he released three landmark albums — My Aim Is True (1977), This Year's Model (1978), and Armed Forces (1979) — each one more ambitious than the last. The Attractions — keyboardist Steve Nieve, bassist Bruce Thomas, and drummer Pete Thomas — became his permanent band and gave his increasingly complex songs an urgent, precise musical vehicle. Costello's work in this period set a standard for literate, politically engaged pop songwriting that few artists have matched.",
