    "artistOverview": "Devo formed at Kent State University in Akron, Ohio, in the early 1970s — partly as a response to the 1970 shooting of student protesters on campus by National Guard troops. The band developed a concept called 'de-evolution': the idea that humanity is moving backward, not forward, and that modern society was proof. They dressed in matching uniforms, performed with robotic precision, and made satirical pop music that questioned whether freedom, individuality, and progress were real. Despite being one of the strangest bands in mainstream rock, they landed a top-40 hit with 'Whip It' and influenced virtually every synth-pop and new wave act that followed.",
