    "artistOverview": "Danger Mouse is the production alias of Brian Joseph Burton, a New York-born producer and musician who became one of the most versatile and in-demand producers in music after The Grey Album brought him international attention in 2004. Burton is known for his ability to move between genres — from hip-hop to indie rock to baroque pop — while maintaining a consistent sensibility that prioritizes mood, texture, and unexpected combinations. He has produced for Gorillaz, Beck, Adele, U2, and Red Hot Chili Peppers, and co-created Gnarls Barkley and Broken Bells.",
