    "artistYearsActive": "1991 – 2006",
    "artistOverview": "J Dilla — born James Dewitt Yancey in Detroit — is widely considered one of the greatest hip-hop producers who ever lived. He spent the 1990s producing hits for A Tribe Called Quest, Erykah Badu, Janet Jackson, The Pharcyde, and Common while developing a deeply personal style characterized by deliberately off-beat drums, thick layered samples, and an emotional warmth unlike any other producer of his era. In 2005 he was diagnosed with lupus and a rare blood disorder called TTP. He spent the last years of his life in and out of the hospital in Los Angeles, finishing Donuts in his hospital room from his bed. He died on February 10, 2006 — three days after the album's release.",
