    "discussionQuestions": [
        "Donuts has no words, no singers, no rap verses. Can an album of beats be emotional? Did any of the tracks make you feel something specific?",
        "Dilla made this album while dying in a hospital. Does that context change how you hear the music — or should music stand on its own, without biography?",
        "The tracks average less than 90 seconds each. Why would a producer make beats that short? What does brevity do that a longer song can't?",
        "Questlove said Dilla changed the entire language of hip-hop. After listening to Donuts, do you believe that a single person can change what music sounds like?"
    ],
