        "Live Through This was released on April 12, 1994 — four days after Kurt Cobain's death. Every song on the album was written before he died.",
        "The album was produced by Sean Slade and Paul Q. Kolderie and recorded entirely in 1993; the circumstances of its release had nothing to do with how it was made.",
        "Hole formed in Los Angeles in 1989. Bassist Kristen Pfaff, who played on the album, died of a heroin overdose two months after the album's release, in June 1994.",
        "Despite the chaotic circumstances surrounding its release, the album received strong reviews and reached #52 on the Billboard 200, eventually being certified platinum in the United States."
