    "keySongs": [
        {
            "title": "Violet",
            "note": "The album's opening track sets up the dynamic that runs through everything: quiet menace building into an explosive release. Listen for the shift between verse and chorus — it's the whole album in miniature."
        },
        {
            "title": "Doll Parts",
            "note": "The most melodic and direct song here — almost a straightforward ballad. The lyric 'I want to be the girl with the most cake' is one of the most discussed lines on the album. What does it actually mean?"
        },
        {
            "title": "Asking for It",
            "note": "Written from direct personal experience. The title uses the phrase that is used to dismiss victims of assault. Does knowing that context change how you hear the song?"
        },
        {
            "title": "Miss World",
            "note": "Built around the beauty pageant as metaphor — someone being looked at rather than seen. How does Love use irony to get at something real?"
        }
    ],
