    "discussionQuestions": [
        "Live Through This came out four days after Kurt Cobain's death. Does knowing that change how you hear it — and should it? Is there a difference between context that illuminates a record and context that hijacks it?",
        "Courtney Love was one of the most vilified figures in 1990s rock. How much does public hostility toward an artist affect how their work gets heard — and does it wear off over time?",
        "'Asking for It' was written after Love was assaulted in a crowd. Does knowing the biographical source of a song change its meaning, or does the song have to stand on its own?",
        "The album moves between raw aggression and melodic vulnerability. Is that contrast a weakness — inconsistency — or is it the whole point?"
    ],
