        "Rum, Sodomy & the Lash was produced by Elvis Costello, who had been a fan of the band and wanted to capture their live energy while bringing more musical cohesion to their recordings.",
        "The title is a phrase attributed to Winston Churchill, said to describe the traditions of the British navy — the Pogues used it to frame an album full of sea shanties, murder ballads, and emigrant laments.",
