            "teacherNote": "An Australian anti-war ballad written by Eric Bogle in 1971 about the Gallipoli campaign. The Pogues' version is nearly eight minutes long — a full commitment to the song's emotional scale. One of the most powerful anti-war songs in the folk tradition."
