    "artistOverview": "David Bowie was a British singer, songwriter, and performer whose career spanned five decades and encompassed an extraordinary range of musical styles and personas. He began as a mod-influenced singer in the 1960s, became a glam rock icon with Ziggy Stardust in 1972, pivoted to soul and funk in 1975, collaborated with Brian Eno on the Berlin Trilogy in the late 1970s, and continued reinventing himself until his final album Blackstar, released two days before his death in January 2016. Diamond Dogs represents the end of his glam era and the beginning of his transition toward something harder to classify.",
