        "George Michael wrote, produced, and performed almost everything on Faith himself at the age of 24 — the first full demonstration of his abilities outside of Wham!",
        "The title track samples 'Twenty Flight Rock' by Eddie Cochran (1958) — a deliberate reference to American rockabilly tradition by a British pop artist at a moment when most pop was synthesizer-driven.",
        "Faith was the first album by a white British solo artist to reach #1 on the US R&B albums chart, and spawned four US #1 singles: 'Faith', 'Father Figure', 'One More Try', and 'Monkey'.",
