    "keySongs": [
        {
            "title": "Faith",
            "note": "The title track opens with a church organ before a rockabilly guitar riff kicks in. Michael is declaring his influences and his independence in the first 30 seconds. What does the choice of sounds tell you about what he's trying to do?"
        },
        {
            "title": "Father Figure",
            "note": "Slow, gospel-tinged, and emotionally complicated. The word 'faith' appears in the lyric. How does Michael use the language of religion to talk about romantic love — and why might that combination be powerful?"
        },
        {
            "title": "One More Try",
            "note": "Often cited as the album's vocal high point. Listen to how Michael controls volume and intensity across the song. What is he doing technically, and what is the emotional effect?"
        },
        {
            "title": "Kissing a Fool",
            "note": "The album closes with a jazz ballad — completely different from how it opened. Does this ending feel earned, or does it feel like a different record entirely? What does it say about George Michael's range?"
        }
    ],
