    "artistOverview": "The Grateful Dead were an American rock band formed in San Francisco in 1965, initially at the heart of the psychedelic counterculture of the late 1960s. Led by guitarist Jerry Garcia — whose lyrical partnership with poet Robert Hunter produced some of the most distinctive songwriting in American rock — the band became famous for live shows that could run four or five hours, with extended improvisational passages that bore little resemblance to their studio recordings. Workingman's Dead, released in 1970, is one of the clearest examples in rock history of a band voluntarily abandoning their own established sound to pursue something more essential.",
