    "artistOverview": "Arcade Fire formed in Montreal, Quebec, in 2001 around husband-and-wife duo Win Butler and Régine Chassagne. They typically perform with seven or more members on stage and switch instruments between songs. Their debut album Funeral (2004) — heard by this club in Week 96 — was written during a period of real family grief; The Suburbs, their third album, turns to a different kind of loss: the feeling of growing up somewhere and leaving it behind, only to find the place still living inside you.",
