    "artistYearsActive": "1978 – 2002, 2011 – present",
    "artistOverview": "Pulp are a Sheffield band formed in 1978 by Jarvis Cocker when he was fourteen years old. After more than fifteen years of near-misses and critical recognition without commercial success, they broke through with His 'n' Hers (1994) and Different Class (1995) — the latter becoming one of the defining albums of the Britpop era, with 'Common People' becoming an anthem about class, aspiration, and authenticity. By the time This Is Hardcore arrived in 1998, Cocker had become one of the most recognisable cultural figures in Britain — and the album records what that actually felt like.",
