    "discussionQuestions": [
        "Cocker spent fifteen years wanting fame and then wrote an album about how strange and hollow it felt when he got it. Is that surprising? Do you think you would feel the same way?",
        "The album is lush, beautiful, almost decadent in its production. Does the quality of the music change how you feel about the bleak things it's saying? Can beautiful music be about ugly feelings?",
        "'A Little Soul' is addressed to Cocker's absent father. It is much more vulnerable than anything else on the album. Why do you think that track ended up on this particular record, about fame and disillusionment?",
        "The album sold less well than Different Class. If you were Jarvis Cocker, would that feel like confirmation of the album's thesis — or would it just feel disappointing?"
    ],
