    "artistOverview": "Modest Mouse formed in Issaquah, Washington, in 1992, when Isaac Brock was a teenager living in difficult circumstances — unstable housing, an itinerant childhood. Brock's lyrics are shaped by that experience: they tend toward themes of displacement, mortality, cosmic scale, and the absurdity of being alive. The Moon & Antarctica was their major-label debut on Epic Records but remains the least commercially oriented thing they ever recorded — a dense, difficult, deeply strange album that many consider one of the greatest indie rock records ever made.",
