    "artistOverview": "Nick Cave & The Bad Seeds formed in Melbourne in 1983 after Cave's previous band The Birthday Party dissolved. Cave moved to Berlin, then London, then Brighton, assembling a rotating collective of musicians — most consistently guitarist and multi-instrumentalist Warren Ellis — around his vision of rock music as gothic, literary storytelling. Cave is as much a novelist, playwright, and poet as a rock musician; he has published fiction, written screenplays, and maintained a newsletter of considerable literary ambition. Murder Ballads, his ninth album, is his most deliberately theatrical and conceptually unified work: an entire album dedicated to the oldest tradition in folk song — stories of crime and consequence.",
