                "note": "The blues tradition of murder ballads — 'Gallows Pole,' 'Midnight Special,' 'Where Did You Sleep Last Night' — is the deepest root of what Cave is drawing on. These were songs that described violence and consequence because that was how the community processed moral facts.",
