    "artistOverview": "Elliott Smith was an American singer-songwriter from Portland, Oregon, known for intimate, quietly devastating songs about heartbreak, addiction, and anxiety. He began as a lo-fi acoustic artist releasing albums on small indie labels, but shot to national attention in 1997 when his song 'Miss Misery' was nominated for an Academy Award after appearing in the film Good Will Hunting. XO was his major label debut — the first time he had the resources to record with full orchestration, session musicians, and a professional studio budget. He died in 2003 at age 34.",
