        "mood": "Tender, melancholy, wistful, quietly devastating — like a conversation you can't stop replaying",
        "mainSounds": "Acoustic and electric guitar, piano, orchestral strings, layered vocals, bass, subtle drums",
        "productionStyle": "Lush and detailed — Smith layered his own vocals and instruments into dense arrangements that sound intimate despite their scale. Rob Schnapf and Tom Rothrock helped translate his acoustic sensibility into a major label sound without losing its emotional directness.",
        "energy": "Quiet to mid — the album rarely raises its voice, but its emotional intensity is constant",
