    "keyFacts": [
        "Smith was nominated for an Academy Award in 1998 for 'Miss Misery,' written for the film Good Will Hunting — he performed it live at the ceremony in a white suit, in front of an audience of a billion people. He lost to Celine Dion's 'My Heart Will Go On.'",
        "XO was Smith's first album recorded with a major label budget. He used the resources to hire session musicians, record full orchestral string arrangements, and layer his vocals and instruments far more densely than on his earlier lo-fi records.",
        "Smith played most of the instruments himself — guitar, bass, piano, drums — building the arrangements by recording one part at a time and layering them. The lush sound is largely the work of one person.",
        "Smith died in October 2003 at age 34. His death was ruled a suicide, though some details remained disputed. His posthumous album From a Basement on the Hill was completed and released in 2004."
    ],
