    "discussionQuestions": [
        "The club heard Either/Or at week 90 — one of Smith's lo-fi acoustic albums made with almost no budget. How does XO compare? Does the lush production make the songs better, or does it change them in ways you didn't expect?",
        "Smith was famously uncomfortable with the mainstream attention he got after the Academy Awards. Does XO sound like an artist who wanted to be famous — or an artist who used the resources to make the record he always wanted to make?",
        "Many of Smith's songs sound beautiful on the surface — the melodies are warm, the arrangements are soft — but the lyrics describe heartbreak, anxiety, and depression. How does the contrast between sound and content affect how you hear the album?",
        "Smith died in 2003, five years after XO was released. Does knowing that change how you listen to this album? Should it? Is it possible to separate an artist's life from their work?"
    ],
