            "title": "Aumgn",
            "note": "The album's most alien track — not a groove piece but a sound environment, seventeen minutes of texture, noise, and strangeness. This is where Can most clearly shows their debt to Stockhausen's avant-garde composition. It is not supposed to be comfortable."
