    "artistYearsActive": "1989 – 1999, 2010, 2022 – present",
    "artistOverview": "Pavement formed in Stockton, California in 1989, built around the songwriting of Stephen Malkmus and Scott Kannberg. They became the defining indie rock band of the early 1990s with their debut Slanted and Enchanted — a lo-fi classic that influenced nearly every guitar band that followed. Their follow-up Crooked Rain, Crooked Rain brought them their closest brush with mainstream attention, with actual radio singles and genuine critical consensus behind them. Wowee Zowee, their third album, was their response: an 18-track sprawl of stylistic experiments, fake country songs, ten-second interludes, and slow-burning epics that critics called unfocused and fans weren't sure what to do with. It is now widely considered their masterpiece.",
