    "classroomSafeMode": true,
    "keyFacts": [
        "Wowee Zowee has 18 tracks and runs nearly 52 minutes — Pavement's longest and most sprawling album. The track lengths range from 30 seconds to over five minutes. The album deliberately resists the idea of a consistent sound or style.",
        "The album was initially received with disappointment by critics who had praised Crooked Rain, Crooked Rain. The NME called it 'a mess.' By the 2000s it was being described as their best album. It is one of the most dramatic examples of a record being misunderstood on first release.",
        "Pavement self-produced Wowee Zowee despite having the budget for outside production by 1995. The rough, unpolished sound is a deliberate choice — the band had become famous partly for their lo-fi aesthetic and refused to abandon it when they had more resources.",
        "Stephen Malkmus reunited Pavement for a tour in 2010 and again in 2022 — more than two decades after their original breakup. The reunion tours played Wowee Zowee in full on some dates, and critics who had dismissed the album in 1995 wrote extensively about what they had missed."
    ],
