    "discussionQuestions": [
        "The club heard Debut at week 97. How does Homogenic compare? What changed in Björk's music between those two albums — and can you hear the trauma in the sound even without knowing the backstory?",
        "The album combines orchestral strings with electronic production in a way that was unusual in 1997. How does that combination affect how the album sounds? Do the strings make it feel warmer, or does the electronic production make the strings feel colder?",
        "'Pluto' is the album's most explosive and violent-sounding track, and 'All Is Full of Love' is the most tender. The album ends on tenderness. Does that ending feel earned — or does it feel too easy after everything that came before?",
        "Homogenic was made in direct response to personal trauma. Can you tell? Does knowing the backstory change how you hear the album — or should music be able to stand on its own without that context?"
    ],
