            "artist": "Tori Amos",
            "year": 1996,
            "teaser": "Next week we stay with a female artist using music to process and reclaim power — but where Björk works with electronic production and orchestral strings, Tori Amos recorded her album in a church in Ireland and a plantation house in New Orleans, playing harpsichord and clavichord, and made something almost entirely on her own terms.",
            "listenForQuestion": "What does it mean to make an album about taking your power back — and how do you make that sound like music rather than a manifesto?"
