    "artistYearsActive": "1980 – present",
    "artistOverview": "Tori Amos is an American singer, songwriter, and pianist from North Carolina whose music combines classical piano technique with confessional, literary lyrics and a theatrical performance style unlike anything else in pop music. The club heard her debut Little Earthquakes at week 89 — an album about surviving trauma that announced one of the most distinctive voices in 1990s music. Boys for Pele is her third album, made in the aftermath of the end of a significant personal relationship, and produced entirely by herself. She played almost every instrument, including historical keyboard instruments like harpsichord and clavichord, recorded the album in unconventional spaces, and made something so sonically and emotionally extreme that it remains the most challenging and celebrated record of her career.",
