    "discussionQuestions": [
        "The club heard Little Earthquakes at week 89 — Tori's debut, also a record about surviving trauma. How does Boys for Pele compare? Has the sound of her processing changed, or just the instrumentation?",
        "The album uses instruments — harpsichord, clavichord — that you almost never hear in pop music. Why do you think Tori made that choice? What do those sounds do to the emotional register of the music?",
        "Boys for Pele was Tori's first self-produced album. Does it sound like a record made without compromise? What do you notice that might not have survived if a producer had been hired to shape it?",
        "Both Björk (Homogenic, last week) and Tori Amos (this week) made albums about trauma and reclamation in the mid-1990s. What do those albums have in common — and where do they differ? What does the comparison tell you about how different artists process the same kind of experience?"
    ],
