        {
            "title": "Tightrope",
            "note": "The album's most infectious track — a funk groove featuring Big Boi that hides a message about staying balanced and grounded in the face of pressure."
        },
        {
            "title": "Cold War",
            "note": "Monáe nearly cries in the music video's single unbroken take. The song asks directly: 'Do you know what you're fighting for?' Listen for the answer she gives."
        },
        {
            "title": "Oh, Maker",
            "note": "The album's quietest and most vulnerable moment — stripped back to almost nothing, it's where Cindi Mayweather's story becomes most human."
        },
        {
            "title": "BaBopByeYa",
            "note": "An eight-minute jazz epic to close the album — after everything, Monáe ends not with a statement but with pure musical flight."
        }
