        "Fugazi stopped concerts to address violence in the crowd. Is that an artist's responsibility — to police their own audience? Where does a band's ethical obligation end?",
        "This album came out the same year as Nirvana's In Utero — and Fugazi were turning down major label millions. Why do you think they refused? What did they gain by staying independent?"
