    "discussionQuestions": [
        "Sandinista! has 36 tracks and runs 144 minutes. Is that a creative achievement or an act of self-indulgence — or can it be both at the same time?",
        "'The Magnificent Seven' is widely considered one of the first rock records to use hip-hop rhythms and rap-style vocals. Does knowing that change how you hear it?",
        "The Clash took no royalties on the first 200,000 copies to force a lower price for fans. Is that a meaningful political act or a gesture that ultimately changes nothing?",
        "We heard London Calling in week 35. How does Sandinista! compare — is it better, worse, more ambitious, less focused? What does comparing them tell you about what the Clash were trying to do?"
    ],
