    "artistOverview": "The B-52s formed in Athens, Georgia in 1976 and became one of the most joyfully weird bands in American rock history — a group that combined thrift-store fashion, alien references, party-record energy, and genuinely experimental song structures into a sound entirely their own. Their early career was defined by the guitar playing of Ricky Wilson, who developed a unique tuning style that gave the band its distinctive chiming, hypnotic sound. When Wilson died of AIDS in 1985, the band went silent. Cosmic Thing was their return, and it became the biggest commercial success of their career.",
