    "discussionQuestions": [
        "The B-52s lost their guitarist to AIDS and spent years in silence before making this record. Does knowing that change how 'Love Shack' sounds to you — does the joy feel different with that context?",
        "Joy and grief are usually treated as opposites. Can a piece of art hold both at the same time? Is Cosmic Thing an example of that?",
        "The B-52s were openly queer-identified artists making music during the AIDS crisis. How much of that context should we bring to a party record?",
        "Keith Strickland had to learn an entirely new instrument after Ricky Wilson died. How do you think loss can force someone to grow into something they weren't before?"
    ],
