    "artistOverview": "Erykah Badu is a Dallas-born singer, songwriter, and producer widely regarded as the queen of neo-soul — a movement that fused classic soul and R&B with hip-hop production and a deeply personal, philosophically conscious lyrical approach. Her 1997 debut Baduizm announced a completely original voice in Black American music, and she has spent the decades since deepening and complicating that voice while refusing to make the same record twice. She is also one of the most conceptually ambitious artists working in any genre, treating each album as a unified artistic statement rather than a collection of songs.",
